transcript.text: Hello everyone, welcome back to our On Print Shop tutorial series.
In this video, we will walk you through the process of creating products with a fixed quantity in price.
This feature is incredibly useful for offering standardized products to your customers, where you can define a fixed price for the fixed quantity of a product.
For instance, if a customer chooses to buy 500 quantities of a product, the fixed price you have defined will be displayed for that.
Similarly, when the quantity is increased to 1000, the price will change accordingly.
Now, let's check how you can offer this pricing to your customers.
To get started, log into your On Print Shop account and navigate to the Product section.
Click on the Add button to begin creating a new product.
In the Add Product page, enter the relevant details such as the product name, product type, and category.
Now, in the price defining method, select the first option, Fixed Quantity and Price.
Define the other relevant details and click on the Save and Continue button from the top.
Add the product description to the Description tab and save the changes.
Now let's move forward to the Designer tab.
Here you need to define the sizes of the products that you will offer to your customers and save the details to add the price for different product sizes added.
First add the quantities and then enter the pricing for the respective sizes.
You can also enter the quantity and price in bulk using the Add Bulk data.
Once done, save the pricing details and add other relevant details for the product.
That's it.
You have successfully created a product with a fixed quantity in price.
If you have any questions, our support executives are here to help.
Just reach out through live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
